# Title capitalization

Use **title case** for headings, section titles, dialog titles, and prominent UI labels.

## Capitalize

- Nouns, verbs, adjectives, adverbs, pronouns
- First and last word of the title (always)
- Words four letters or longer (even if they would normally be lowercase)

## Lowercase (filler / minor words)

Keep these lowercase **unless** they are the first or last word:

`a`, `an`, `the`, `and`, `but`, `or`, `nor`, `for`, `so`, `yet`, `at`, `by`, `in`, `of`, `on`, `to`, `up`, `as`, `per`, `via`, `vs`

## Examples

```
// Good
Add Friends
Your Code
How It Works
Cite Your Draft
Settings

// Bad
Add friends
your code
How it works
Cite your draft
```

## Scope

- Page titles (`h1`), section titles (`h2`/`h3`), panel headings, tab labels, dialog titles
- Button labels that act as titles (e.g. section subtitles like "Your Code")
- Skip: body copy, error messages, placeholders, sentence-case descriptions

## Title + description spacing

On **logged-in app pages** (`app/(app)/` and their components), wrap a heading and its description in `.pg-title-copy` (6px gap via `--title-desc-gap`, matching Delete Account in Settings).

Do **not** use `.pg-title-copy` on auth pages (`app/(auth)/` login, onboarding).

```tsx
<div className="pg-title-copy">
  <h2>Section Title</h2>
  <p className="pg-muted">Description sentence here.</p>
</div>
```
